elancer network\t50-100 unique ad creatives across all territories in vertical format\tVisual diversity test: no two ads look similar at thumbnail level\tWeeks 5-7 2.3\tWrite Benefit-Focused Ad Copy (100+ variations)\tCreative Intelligence Agent\tWrite copy using framework: Hook (problem) → Agitate (consequences) → Solution (product) → CTA (quiz link) → Test emotional vs. logical angles → Focus on outcomes (confidence, privacy, convenience) not features (pills, delivery)\tProduct benefits, customer testimonials, pain point research\t100+ ad copy variations in Google Doc with performance prediction scores\tCopy passes brand voice test, clear differentiation between angles\tWeek 6 2.4\tUpload & Organize in Meta Library\tCreative Testing Strategist\tCreate naming convention: [Territory][Format][Hook]_[Date] → Upload all creatives to Meta Ads Manager → Tag each ad with territory, concept, format → Create thumbnail view for quick reference\tAll creative assets, ad copy doc\tOrganized ad library with 50-100 ads tagged and ready for deployment\tCan filter by territory/format in <10 seconds\tWeek 7 2.5\tLaunch Initial Testing Phase (Week 1)\tCreative Testing Strategist\tLaunch 20-30 ads in Sales Campaign → Budget: $200-500 per ad set → Let run untouched for 7 days → Monitor CPMr, CTR, Hook Rate (3-sec video views), CPA daily\tCreative assets, campaign structure, testing budget ($5K-10K)\t20-30 ads live and collecting data\tAll ads spending evenly, no delivery issues, data flowing to dashboard\tWeek 8, Days 1-7 2.6\tAnalyze Results & Kill Losers\tCreative Testing Strategist\tAfter 7 days → Export performance data → Identify bottom 70% performers (high CPMr, low CTR/ROAS) → Turn off underperformers → Keep top 30% running → Document why winners won\t7-day performance data exported from Meta\tPerformance analysis report with winners/losers identified and insights documented\tClear pattern emerges on which territories/hooks resonate\tWeek 8, Day 8 2.7\tScale Winners & Regenerate