ive concepts (territories) not just creative variations (hooks) Your Iteration: Map 10 distinct creative territories that feel radically different Implementation: Film festival approach—cinematic founder story, chaotic meme comparison, lo-fi UGC, motion graphics, nostalgic throwback Unique Angle: If all ads look the same at thumbnail level, you're burning budget Framework 3: The Three-Campaign Simplification Proven Concept: 2026 = death of complexity. One sales campaign beats 10+ ad sets Your Iteration: 1 Sales (CBO Advantage+), 1 Awareness (Video), 1 Remarketing Implementation: Consolidation gives Andromeda algorithm room to learn fast Unique Angle: Fewer campaigns with more creative ideas Framework 4: AI-Powered Creative Regeneration Loop Proven Concept: Upload best ads + performance data to Gemini → Analyze why they worked → Generate new concepts Your Iteration: Weekly cadence: Launch → Run 7 days → Kill losers → Feed learnings to AI → Regenerate Implementation: AI isn't replacing creative—it's giving creative teams x-ray vision Unique Angle: 80% creative operations, 20% media buying Framework 5: Subscription-as-Service Model Proven Concept: Free consultation + product bundle = normalized longer commitment Your Iteration: AI-powered refill timing = service moment, not sales message Implementation: Track usage patterns → Send reminders 3-5 days before run-out → Personalize messaging Unique Angle: Doesn't just deliver products—maintains connection to expertise 🎨 VISUAL PROCESS FLOWCHARTS I'll create comprehensive visual flowcharts to map out these processes for you: Using Tool | Image Generation Professional business flowchart infographic showing \"Hims & Hers E-Commerce Strategy System\" with 5 interconnected pillars: 1) DISTRIBUTION (Meta Ads icon with 1000+ ads symbol) 2) QUIZ FUNNEL (questionnaire icon with personalization symbols) 3) PERSONALIZATION (AI brain icon with customer segments) 4) DECISION ENGINE (website/landing page icon with trust badges) 5) OUTCO